>
  <section>
    <h2>Project Background</h2>
    <p>
      Nantian Gateway was born from a simple realization: while Kubernetes ingress and API gateways have traditionally been dominated by complex, monolithic architectures or configuration-heavy engines, modern microservices demand simpler, safer, and faster routing infrastructures.
    </p>
    <p>
      We built Nantian Gateway to combine the rich, production-tested ecosystem of Go (for controlling and interpreting Kubernetes cluster states) with the blazing-fast, memory-safe, and GC-less runtime of Rust (for handling active data-plane traffic). By keeping configuration aligned strictly with standard <strong>Kubernetes Gateway API (v1.5.1)</strong> specifications, we eliminate custom CRDs and proprietary configuration structures, offering a standardized approach.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Our Vision</h2>
    <p>
      Our vision is to empower cloud-native teams with a unified gateway that solves traditional routing while serving as a secure, fast **AI Gateway** out of the box. We believe in open-source standards, deep performance optimization (leveraging Pingora), and extensibility through a modern Wasm-based plugin ecosystem.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Maintainers & Community</h2>
    <p>
      Nantian Gateway is actively developed and maintained by the <strong>Nantian Gateway Open Source Community</strong>. We are a collection of cloud-native engineers, platform developers, and AI researchers passionate about high-performance networking and Kubernetes.
    </p>
    <p>
      As a community-driven project, we welcome contributions of all forms—including documentation, code, design, issues, and discussions. You can find us and join our conversations on our official GitHub repository.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Join the Journey</h2>
    <p>
      Whether you are looking to deploy a high-performance ingress controller for millions of requests, secure your AI API keys with rate-limiting, or explore our Wasm plugin engine, we would love to have you onboard. Check out our <a href="/getting-started/quick-start/">Quick Start Guide</a> or connect with us via <a href="https://github.com/nantian-gw/gateway/discussions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Discussions</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
